superheroes.name: SPIDER MAN
superheroes.description: Spider-Man, sometimes translated as Spider-Man, is an American character created by Stan Lee and Steve Ditko,? and introduced in Amazing Fantasy No. 15, published by Marvel Comics in August 1962

superheroes.name: Fantastic Four
superheroes.description: The Fantastic Four are formed after four civilian astronauts are exposed to cosmic rays during an unauthorized test flight into outer space in an experimental rocket designed by Dr. Reed Richards

superheroes.name: Captain America
superheroes.description: Captain America was designed as a patriotic supersoldier who frequently fought against the Axis powers in World War II, and was Timely Comics' most popular character during the war period

superheroes.name: Iron Man
superheroes.description: Iron Man (known in English as Iron Man) is a superhero appearing in American comic books published by Marvel Comics. The character was co-created by writer and editor Stan Lee and screenwriter Larry Lieber. He was designed by artists Don Heck and Jack Kirby

superheroes.name: The X Patrol
superheroes.description: It all began in 1963, when Marvel published Stan Lee and Jack Kirby's The X-Men. Most of the original members appeared in the first issue, but we find out how they joined Xavier's team through flashbacks in the years to come. Caclops, Iceman, Angel and Beast were the first students. These four, along with Jean Grey a.k.a. Wonder Girl, were the core of the team for the next twelve years

superheroes.name: Hulk
superheroes.description: The son of an abusive father, Bruce Banner grew up shy and introverted, but a scientific genius. As a young man, thanks to his outstanding work in the field of nuclear physics, he attracted the attention of the United States Army who wanted to adapt his theories for weaponry

superheroes.name: Black Panther
superheroes.description: He is the first black-skinned superhero in Marvel history and it should be noted that the character was created prior to the Black Panther Party, which was founded in October of the same year. He is the king and protector of the fictional African nation of Wakanda

superheroes.name: Daredevil
superheroes.description: As a child, Matt Murdock lost his sight and gained superhuman senses in an accident that taught him to live without fear. He then goes to law school, which leads him to a life of crime-fighting in New York City; as a lawyer and as vigilante Daredevil

superheroes.name: Thor
superheroes.description: Thor Odinson is the God of Thunder, former King of New Asgard and founding member of the Avengers. When his irresponsible behaviour threatened the Asgardians into another war with the Frost Giants, he was stripped of his power and banished to Earth by his father, Odan

superheroes.name: The Black Widow
superheroes.description: Natasha was born in Stalingrad (now Volgograd), Russia. The first and best known Black Widow, she is a Russian agent trained as a spy, martial artist and sniper, and equipped with an arsenal of high-tech weapons, including a pair of wrist-mounted energy weapons, and nicknamed Widow's Picket

superheroes.name: Captain Marvel
superheroes.description: Captain Carol Danvers is a former U.S. Air Force pilot who, upon destroying the Light Speed Drive manufactured by her mentor Mar-Vell, was exposed to the energy of the Tesseract, gained cosmic powers, and was abducted to serve the Kree Empire

superheroes.name: The Punisher
superheroes.description: Francis Frank Castle, known as The Punisher, is a fictional character and anti-hero appearing in American comic books published by Marvel Comics. The character was created by writer Gerry Conway and artist John Romita Sr

superheroes.name: Ant-Man and the Wasp
superheroes.description: Created by David Michelinie and John Byrne, Scott Lang first appeared in The Avengers #181 (March 1979) and Marvel Premiere #47 (April 1979) as the second superhero character to use the name Ant-Man in the Marvel Universe. He's a reformed thief and an expert in electranics

superheroes.name: Luke Cage
superheroes.description: Created during the heyday of the Blaxploitation genre, Luke Cage is an ex-con incarcerated for a crime he didn't commit, who gains the powers of superhuman strength and unbreakable skin after voluntarily submitting to an experimental procedure

superheroes.name: Ms. Marvel
superheroes.description: Ms. Marvel (Kamala Khan) is a Pakistani superhero who appears in comic books published by Marvel Comics. Marvel (Kamala Khan) is a Pakistani superhero who appears in comic books published by Marvel Comics. Created by editors Sana Amanat and Stephen Wacker, writer G. Willow Wilson and artist Adrian Alphona, Khan was the first Muslim Marvel character to star in her own comic book

superheroes.name: The Vision
superheroes.description: Visian was created from a copy of the original Human Torch, a synth man created by Phineas T. Horton. Horton. Ultron took this android form and added advanced technology to it, such as robotic programming of his own design and a replica of human brainwaves

superheroes.name: Hawkeye
superheroes.description: Hawkeye was created by Stan Lee and Don Heck at a time when the publisher was striving to create fallible heroes. He made his first appearance in the comic book world in Tales of Suspense in September 1964. Oddly enough, the character was a villain at the time

superheroes.name: Moon Knight
superheroes.description: Moon Knight is a fictional superhero appearing in comic books published by Marvel Comics. He was created by writer Doug Moench and artist Don Perlin, debuted in Wolf-Man by Night #32 (August 1975)?and exists on Earth-616, the main land of the Marvel Universe.

superheroes.name: Namor
superheroes.description: As the mutant son of a human sea captain and a princess from the mystical undersea kingdom of Atlantis, Namor possesses the super-strength and aquatic abilities of the Homo mermanus race, as well as the mutant ability to fly, along with other superhuman powers

superheroes.name: Inhumans
superheroes.description: The Inhumans are led by their king, Black Bolt, and his Royal Family, consisting of Medusa, Karnak, Gorgon, Tritan, Crystal, Maximus the Mad, and the dog Lockjaw. Both Crystal and Medusa have been members of the Fantastic Four; Crystal has also been a member of the Avengers

superheroes.name: Batman
superheroes.description: Creator. Batman is a comic book superhero co-created by artist Bob Kane and writer Bill Finger and published by DC Comics. The character made his first appearance in Detective Comics #27 (May 1939). Batman is the secret identity of Bruce Wayne, a billionaire businessman, heartthrob and philanthropist

superheroes.name: Superman
superheroes.description: Superman (English: Superman) is a fictional superhero who first appeared in the American comic books published by DC Comics. ???? The character was created by American writer Jerry Siegel and Canadian artist Joe Shuster in 1933 when they were both living in Cleveland, Ohio

superheroes.name: Wonder Woman
superheroes.description: She is a warrior princess of the Amazons, a fictional people based on the Amazons of Greek mythology. In her homeland she is known as Princess Diana of Themyscira but outside of Themyscira she uses the secret identity of Diana Prince

superheroes.name: Green Lantern
superheroes.description: In 1940, the lantern will find its way into the hands of Alan Scott, a young engineer. After being the sole survivor of the collapse of a railway bridge and being on the verge of death, the flame will teach Scott how to make a ring from its metal, to give him incredible powers as the superhero Green Lantern

superheroes.name: Swamp Thing
superheroes.powers: plants behave according to their will
superheroes.description: Story: After suffering an attack in his laboratory, the chemist Alec Holland falls into the swamp engulfed in flames and covered by a bio-reactive drug of his invention. From there he re-emerges as a plant creature that everyone calls Swamp Thing

superheroes.name: Constantine
superheroes.description: Known as Hellblazer, Constantine is a working-class, London-based occult detective and con man. A chain-smoker, notorious for his unmitigated cynicism, he is characterised by his deadpan sarcasm, as well as his capacity for ruthless manipulation

superheroes.name: Flash
superheroes.description: Jay Garrick was a college student in 1938 who accidentally inhaled heavy water vapours after taking a smoke break inside his laboratory where he had been working. ? As a result, he discovered that he could run at superhuman speed and had equally fast reflexes

superheroes.name: Rorschach
superheroes.description: Rorschach was perhaps the most disturbing hero ever created for comics. His brutal perception of morality as black-and-white reflects writer Alan Moore's systematic deconstruction of the entire notion of the hero, a popular recurring theme in comics since the 1980s

superheroes.name: Catwoman
superheroes.description: She was created by Bill Finger and Bob Kane, and made her first appearance in Batman #1 (Spring 1940). Her real name, Selina, is derived from the lunar deity Selene. Originally, Catwoman was a thief and Batman's rival in the guise of an old woman, and was known simply as the Cat

superheroes.name: Comedian
superheroes.description: Edward Blake / The ComedianOne of the two government-sanctioned heroes (along with Dr. Manhattan) who remains active after the Keene Act is passed in 1977 to ban superheroes. His murder, which occurs shortly before the first chapter begins, sets the plot of Watchmen in motion

superheroes.name: Flash Wally West
superheroes.description: Wally West, the character was a red-haired, green-eyed boy who was the nephew of Barry Allen's girlfriend, Iris West. During a visit to the central police lab, the accident that gave Barry his powers, was repeated but this time giving them to Wally West.

superheroes.name: Animal Man
superheroes.description: Animal Man (Bernhard Buddy Baker) is a fictional DC Comics character. He first appeared in Strange Adventures No. 180 (September 1965) and was created by Dave Wood and Carmine Infantino.

superheroes.name: Nightwing
superheroes.description: The original Nightwing in DC Comics was an identity assumed by the alien superhero Superman when he was stranded on the Kryptonian city of Kandor with his friend Jimmy Olsen. Inspired by Batman and Robin, the two protect Kandor as the superheroes Nightwing and Flamebird.

superheroes.name: Supergirl
superheroes.description: Supergirl is a superhero native of the planet Krypton, where she was known as Kara Zor-El, and is one of the few survivors of its destruction, along with her cousin Kal-EL

superheroes.name: Aquaman
superheroes.description: Aquaman is the son of the lighthouse keeper Thomas Curry and the queen of Atlantis, Atlanna. At least, that's how it was established in the Silver Age stories. From the Crisis on Infinite Earths series onwards, his origin changed to fully Atlantean. In this new reality, her father is Atlan, a mysterious Atlantean wizard

superheroes.name: Green Arrow
superheroes.description: Story. Green Arrow is a vigilante superhero who fights crime with martial arts, archery and technology. In his secret identity he is Oliver Queen, who lives in Star City as a wealthy billionaire playboy and businessman turned outspoken liberal politician.

superheroes.name: Batwoman
superheroes.description: The modern Batwoman is written as a descendant of Jews and as a lesbian. After the events of DC Rebirth, it is established that Kate Kane is the cousin of Batman's alter ego Bruce Wayne and, therefore, the niece of his mother Martha Wayne

superheroes.name: Kyle Rayner
superheroes.description: Kyle Rayner is a fictional superhero appearing in American comic books published by DC Comics. The character is depicted as being associated with the Green Lantern Corps, an extraterrestrial police force of which he is a former member. Cosplayer playing the character

superheroes.name: Batgirl
superheroes.description: The original Batgirl was created by screenwriter Sheldon Moldoff and appeared in 1961, during the Silver Age. She was the alter-ego of Betty Kane, niece of Kathy Kane, aka Batwoman or Batgirl (in Spanish America). Batwoman and Batgirl were created as romantic counterpoints to Batman and Robin

superheroes.name: Martian Manhunter
superheroes.description: The Martian Manhunter (J'onn J'onzz) is a DC Comics superhero. He first appeared in Detective Comics No. 225 (November 1955), in the short story The Strange Experiment of Dr. Erdel written by Joseph Samachson and illustrated by Joe Certa
